WEBVTT

00:01.602 --> 00:05.339
[ Earl Narrating ] The claw
machine is a popular way
to pass time at the Crab Shack.

00:05.373 --> 00:09.143
- Especially when the rat
gets in it.
- A little more left.

00:09.177 --> 00:12.180
If you can't pick him up
by a foot, go for
the chunky part.

00:12.213 --> 00:16.084
I know what I'm doin'. I gotta
sneak up on him from the back
while he's humping that Grover.

00:16.117 --> 00:19.620
- Now!
- [ Machine Whirring ]

00:22.356 --> 00:24.792
Be careful when you pull him
out of the slot.
He's gonna be angry.

00:24.825 --> 00:27.195
He's not gonna be angry.
I saved him.

00:30.331 --> 00:34.235
- [ Rat Squeaks ]
- Ow!

00:34.268 --> 00:37.705
Maybe I should've let him finish
his business with the Grover
before I took him.

00:37.738 --> 00:41.175
You know the kind of guy
who does nothing
but bad things...

00:41.209 --> 00:43.477
and then wonders why
his life sucks?

00:43.511 --> 00:48.516
Well, that was me.
Every time somethin' good
happened to me,

00:48.549 --> 00:50.584
somethin' bad
was always waitin'
around the corner.

00:52.120 --> 00:53.654
Karma.

00:53.687 --> 00:57.425
That's when I realized
I had to change.

00:57.458 --> 01:00.361
So I made a list
of everything bad
I've ever done,

01:00.394 --> 01:03.164
and, one by one,
I'm gonna make up
for all my mistakes.

01:03.197 --> 01:04.832
I'm just tryin'
to be a better person.

01:04.865 --> 01:07.301
My name is Earl.

01:11.339 --> 01:13.141
[ Joy ]
They are monsters, Darnell.

01:13.174 --> 01:14.842
Those kids
are two little monsters.

01:14.875 --> 01:17.878
They used my going-out
lipstick to draw boobs
on the car headlights again.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.880
Joy, I'm tryin' to work.

01:19.913 --> 01:22.183
Sweetheart, you're picking
crabmeat out of claws.

01:22.216 --> 01:24.552
It's not like you're
in a hospital doing
a kidney transplantation.

01:24.585 --> 01:27.455
[ Earl Narrating ]
There were a few things I missed
about being married to Joy.

01:27.488 --> 01:29.490
Her children
were not two of 'em.

01:29.523 --> 01:32.760
Boys get into trouble, Joy.
That's what they do.

01:32.793 --> 01:35.496
- Tell her, Earl.
- Oh, I'm just, uh--

01:35.529 --> 01:37.831
I'm j-- gettin' a beer,
and the rat's back
in the--

01:37.865 --> 01:41.269
What are you askin' him for?
He was worse at disciplinin'
those kids than you are.

01:41.302 --> 01:44.338
[ Earl Narrating ]
She was right.

01:51.312 --> 01:54.215
I always found it best
not to get too involved.

01:55.483 --> 01:57.251
[ Man ]
There you go.

01:57.285 --> 01:59.420
Well, I'm sure
if you put your
two heads together,

01:59.453 --> 02:01.755
you'll be able to,
uh--

02:01.789 --> 02:04.192
Good luck.

02:04.225 --> 02:06.327
[ Earl Narrating ]
I felt bad for Darnell.

02:06.360 --> 02:09.663
But I felt good for me. Those
kids were no longer my problem.

02:09.697 --> 02:13.201
Those kids are beyond fixin'.
They wouldn't even accept 'em
over at the rotten kids camp.

02:13.234 --> 02:15.236
I mean, I ran out of space
on the application.

02:15.269 --> 02:17.838
How bad do they
have to be?

02:17.871 --> 02:20.774
- Are you talking about
the Right Choice Ranch?
- Yeah.

02:20.808 --> 02:23.777
- Whose last name did you put
on the application?
- Yours. Hickey.

02:23.811 --> 02:26.414
That's their legal last name.
Dr. Crabmeat here...

02:26.447 --> 02:28.749
hasn't come up with the $180
to change their names yet.

02:28.782 --> 02:33.254
- Seems like a waste.
I like Hickey.
- [ Exhales ] Damn it.

02:33.287 --> 02:37.958
[ Earl Narrating ] That's when
I realized what I thought wasn't
my problem, actually was.

02:37.991 --> 02:41.595
Number 164--
burned down a barn
at the Right Choice Ranch.

02:44.832 --> 02:48.269
You see, as children,
me and Randy got into
a little trouble here and there.

02:48.302 --> 02:50.504
[ Groaning ]

02:56.510 --> 03:01.215
And our parents didn't seem
to be very entertained
by our antics.

03:01.249 --> 03:05.253
Eventually they had no choice
but to take Randy and me
to the Right Choice Ranch.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.855
It was a nice little camp
that helped troubled kids
turn their lives around.

03:07.888 --> 03:11.392
However, their slogan
raised some eyebrows.

03:12.593 --> 03:15.963
Over the years
they tried new slogans,

03:15.996 --> 03:18.198
but they never
could get it right.

03:22.270 --> 03:24.405
[ Man ]
The Right Choice is,
hands on your head.

03:25.706 --> 03:28.208
The Right Choice is,
hands on your knees.

03:29.610 --> 03:31.545
The Right Choice is,
hands in the air.

03:33.747 --> 03:36.384
[ Earl Narrating ]
Within a few hours, we were
already startin' to learn...

03:36.417 --> 03:37.951
that you didn't have to be bad
to have fun.
[ Shouts ]

03:39.753 --> 03:42.423
We also learned
that Randy was afraid of birds.

03:44.292 --> 03:47.227
[ Quacking ]

03:48.762 --> 03:51.732
[ Shouting ]

03:54.402 --> 03:57.638
Then, which brings us
back to the list,
there was an accident.

03:57.671 --> 03:59.873
I had only recently
taken up smokin',

03:59.907 --> 04:02.710
and properly disposing
of my cigarette butts...

04:02.743 --> 04:04.712
was a habit I hadn't mastered.

04:04.745 --> 04:07.014
They sent Randy and I packing.

04:07.047 --> 04:10.418
Any chance of us being reformed
went up in flames.

04:10.451 --> 04:13.387
Now Joy's kids shouldn't
have to pay for my mistakes.

04:13.421 --> 04:15.489
No, they're gonna have plenty
of their own to pay for.

04:15.523 --> 04:17.925
You're going to a farm?
Shh.

04:17.958 --> 04:20.661
I'm not tellin' Randy.
He's afraid of chickens.

04:20.694 --> 04:23.364
And the pope's big hat.
But mainly 'cause he thinks
there's a chicken under it.

04:23.397 --> 04:25.999
Can I go?
I worked on a farm
growing up.

04:26.033 --> 04:28.035
Oh, yeah?
Where was it?
I don't know.

04:28.068 --> 04:30.671
We were always blindfolded
when they took us there.

04:30.704 --> 04:33.040
But I know they shot
my father in San Pascual,

04:33.073 --> 04:35.343
so it must have been
north of the river of blood.

04:37.010 --> 04:39.913
Man!
A surprise destination.

04:39.947 --> 04:42.883
Give me a hint, Earl.
Like, has funnel cakes.

04:42.916 --> 04:45.519
Okay.
Does not have
funnel cakes.

04:46.787 --> 04:50.624
Does not have
funnel cakes.
Okay.

04:50.658 --> 04:53.060
[ Earl Narrating ]
I didn't like trickin' Randy,

04:53.093 --> 04:55.329
but I was hoping he might
conquer his fear of birds.

04:55.363 --> 04:57.931
He's never grown out of it.

05:00.033 --> 05:03.737
- [ Bird Squawks ]
- Hey, Earl. Did you see
what that stupid bird--

05:03.771 --> 05:06.807
- [ Shouts ]
- [ Thuds ]

05:11.645 --> 05:15.649
Right Choice Ranch?
Yep. Does not have
funnel cakes.

05:15.683 --> 05:18.919
I'm gonna cross
that burned barn off my list.
You okay with that?

05:18.952 --> 05:22.690
Yeah. 'Course.
Why wouldn't I be?
[ Rooster Crows ]

05:22.723 --> 05:25.726
Earl, that was a rooster.
That's a man chicken.

05:25.759 --> 05:28.962
They're the meanest of 'em all.
They got that red flappy thing
under their mouth.

05:28.996 --> 05:31.064
I don't even know
what they make that out of.

05:33.501 --> 05:36.069
I'm afraid of birds,
and I don't care
what you think of me.

05:36.103 --> 05:39.940
It's okay. We all have
our fears. I'm afraid
of snakes and rape.

05:39.973 --> 05:42.976
Come on.
Let's go find the farmer.

05:43.010 --> 05:46.113
[ Crowing Continues ]

05:46.146 --> 05:49.583
I can't remember. With chickens,
are you supposed to play dead
or punch 'em in the nose?

05:52.119 --> 05:54.955
Well, I'll be.

05:54.988 --> 05:57.791
Earl Hickey.
We've been tellin' everybody
around here you're dead.

05:57.825 --> 06:00.060
Nope. Not dead yet.

06:00.093 --> 06:04.465
But my heart did stop briefly
back in 1992 when I got stepped
on at a Motörhead concert.

06:04.498 --> 06:06.734
No, it's not that.
It's just that...

06:06.767 --> 06:09.703
- when we tell the kids the
legend of the barn-burner--
- [ Chicken Clucking ]

06:09.737 --> 06:12.906
we think it's kinda
nice to finish it
with you bein' dead.

06:12.940 --> 06:16.644
Shot in the face actually.
Really? I have a legend?

06:16.677 --> 06:19.146
And a plaque.
Oh.

06:23.116 --> 06:25.152
You're the example
the counselors use...

06:25.185 --> 06:28.155
for someone who made
the wro choice...

06:28.188 --> 06:30.491
here at the
Right Choice Ranch.

06:30.524 --> 06:32.426
Hey, Bud,

06:32.460 --> 06:35.062
little Hector said
that seeing that
baby lamb get born...

06:35.095 --> 06:37.698
has convinced him
to laser off
his teardrop tattoo.

06:37.731 --> 06:41.635
Hey, okay, Hector.
¡Bueno! !Bueno!

06:41.669 --> 06:45.005
Oh, this here's Bobby.
He was probably at the camp
when you were.

06:45.038 --> 06:47.475
He was brought here when
he pulled out all the teeth
from his brother.

06:47.508 --> 06:50.010
He's a successful
businessman now.

06:50.043 --> 06:52.212
He comes here
and volunteers
on weekends.

06:52.245 --> 06:55.783
Earl here's thinkin'
of making up for burnin'
down our barn.

06:55.816 --> 06:59.887
Yep. Gotta undo all
the bad things I did
so I can have a better life.

06:59.920 --> 07:03.924
Well, if you're looking to make
up for burnin' the barn, we sure
could use a proper ostrich pen.

07:03.957 --> 07:06.594
- You guys have an ostrich?
- Yeah.

07:06.627 --> 07:09.630
We got him for the
"Racism Is Having Your Head
in the Sand" bonfire.

07:09.663 --> 07:12.800
We put a little K.K.K. hood
on him and let him chase
the kids around.

07:12.833 --> 07:16.937
All right then.
I'll build that racist
ostrich a pen.

07:16.970 --> 07:19.907
Maybe the campers will learn
somethin' by seeing Earl Hickey
do some good.

07:19.940 --> 07:22.643
- There you go.
- Just do me a favor.

07:22.676 --> 07:25.613
Don't mention to my brother
that there's an ostrich
roamin' around.

07:27.047 --> 07:28.882
[ Clucking ]

07:38.225 --> 07:40.828
What are you gonna do now,
you stupid bird?
I'm behind a fence.

07:42.663 --> 07:45.065
Stupid chick--
[ Warbles ]

07:45.098 --> 07:48.001
[ Softly ]
I don't wanna punch you
in the nose, big chicken,

07:48.035 --> 07:50.003
so I'm just gonna lay down
and die now.

07:50.037 --> 07:51.805
Okay?
Here I am dyin'.

08:02.049 --> 08:04.217
[ Whispering ]
Call the police.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.556
No, no.
G-G-Go call the police.

08:11.158 --> 08:13.961
[ Earl Narrating ]
Building an ostrich pen
actually felt pretty good.

08:13.994 --> 08:16.764
But not as good as seeing
all the faces of the campers...

08:16.797 --> 08:18.799
gettin' inspired
by my positive example.

08:18.832 --> 08:21.234
They couldn't keep
their eyes off me.

08:27.641 --> 08:30.110
- Randy, give me the nail gun.
- No, no. I-I need it.

08:30.143 --> 08:32.680
For what?
You're not doin'
a damn thing.

08:33.781 --> 08:35.716
[ Shouts ]
[ Nail Gun Firing ]

08:36.917 --> 08:38.852
I think I got one
in his McNugget.

08:38.886 --> 08:42.022
- You can have it now.
- [ Boys Bickering,
Indistinct ]

08:42.055 --> 08:44.792
You know what? If y'all
don't stop fightin', I swear
to God I'll slap you so hard,

08:44.825 --> 08:46.594
you'll both switch colors.

08:46.627 --> 08:49.262
- Hey, Earl.
- Hey, Crab Man.

08:49.296 --> 08:52.766
This place is crazy, huh?
It's like a farm or somethin'.

08:52.800 --> 08:55.636
- What are you doin' here?
- Well, you must be doin'
somethin' right,

08:55.669 --> 08:58.839
'cause they called us up
and told us we could bring
the boys up here.

08:58.872 --> 09:02.042
Careful with that sander, honey.
You don't wanna injure
your toilet-scrubbing hand.

09:02.075 --> 09:05.245
Quiero agradecer
a todo el público latino
que nos acompaña cada semana,

09:05.278 --> 09:08.782
y para los que no son latino,
les felicito
por aprender otra idioma.

09:08.816 --> 09:11.051
Sorry, sweetheart.
I don't speak maid.

09:13.787 --> 09:15.756
We're gonna need
Dodge's birthday.

09:15.789 --> 09:18.125
June--

09:18.158 --> 09:19.893
Wait. Do me a favor.
What's this say?

09:21.194 --> 09:23.363
That's a Smurfette
ridin' a skateboard.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.899
No. Under that?

09:25.933 --> 09:28.101
- Oh, June 10.
- Mmm, that's it.

09:29.970 --> 09:32.740
- What about Earl Jr.?
- Darnell?

09:34.074 --> 09:36.977
April 3.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.046
[ Earl Narrating ]
With Catalina's help,

09:39.079 --> 09:41.181
I finished the ostrich pen
a lot sooner than I thought.

09:42.650 --> 09:45.152
Well, I think
I can cross this one off.

09:45.185 --> 09:47.320
I'll go get us some fresh water.

09:47.354 --> 09:51.124
As a child, they wouldn't
let us drink from the well
because of the bodies.

09:51.158 --> 09:54.227
Look, Earl.
They're playin' Right Choice.
Remember that?

09:54.261 --> 09:57.631
Right Choice is,
hands on your nose.

09:57.665 --> 10:00.133
Right Choice is,
stand on one foot.

10:00.167 --> 10:02.670
- All right. Now punch
your neighbor's arm.
- Ow!

10:02.703 --> 10:05.238
- I didn't say "Right Choice."
- [ All Laugh ]

10:08.676 --> 10:10.711
[ Bobby ]
Right Choice is,
hands on your nose.

10:10.744 --> 10:13.947
Trick is, you just watch
what everybody else is doin'
and do what they do.

10:15.849 --> 10:18.819
[ Earl Narrating ]
I'm not sure why,
but that's when it hit me.

10:18.852 --> 10:21.889
I didn't just screw up
my own future by burning down
that barn,

10:21.922 --> 10:24.224
I screwed up Randy's too.

10:26.259 --> 10:30.063
I'm puttin' you
on the list.
What?

10:30.097 --> 10:32.332
I'm puttin' you
on the list.

10:32.365 --> 10:35.268
When I got us thrown out
of here, I didn't just
destroy that barn,

10:35.302 --> 10:37.671
I destroyed your chance
to be a better person.

10:37.705 --> 10:41.341
I gotta put you on the list.
No, no, Earl. I'm glad
we got thrown out of here.

10:41.374 --> 10:44.344
This place is total chaos.
I saw a pig eatin'
his own poo.

10:44.377 --> 10:48.015
But, Randy, if I didn't get us
kicked out, you could've had
a completely different life.

10:48.048 --> 10:50.851
Now look at that guy
Bobby over there.

10:50.884 --> 10:55.455
Perfectly pleated khakis.
Havin' a good job. Flossin'.
That could've been you.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.758
I don't wanna be
that guy, Earl.
I don't wanna floss.

10:57.791 --> 11:00.193
It makes my tongue hurt.
Randy, give me the pen.

11:00.227 --> 11:02.830
No.
You're goin'
on the list, Randy!

11:02.863 --> 11:04.898
I don't wanna!
It's not up to you.
It's up to karma!

11:04.932 --> 11:06.466
[ Nail Gun Fires ]

11:06.499 --> 11:10.303
[ Groans, Screams ]

11:10.337 --> 11:13.373
Mother, mother, mother,
mother, mother, mother,
mother, mother, mother,

11:14.374 --> 11:16.243
Mother!

11:16.276 --> 11:18.345
Pull it out.
Pull it out!

11:18.378 --> 11:20.914
Karma did this, Randy,
'cause you're not
on the list.

11:20.948 --> 11:22.449
Put yourself
on the list!
No!

11:22.482 --> 11:24.217
Do it!
No!

11:24.251 --> 11:25.986
Do it!
Do it!
No!

11:26.019 --> 11:29.422
I burned down
the barn, okay!
I did it. It wasn't you.

11:29.456 --> 11:31.424
[ Earl Narrating ]
Randy wasn't lyin'.

11:31.458 --> 11:33.293
Though he had been
for quite a few years.

11:36.329 --> 11:38.866
Hey, Earl.
Can I have
a drag of that?

11:38.899 --> 11:42.903
No. You're not old enough.
No smokin' till you're 10.

11:42.936 --> 11:46.774
Come on. Let's go inside.
We're gonna play a game of
Duck Duck Everyone's a Winner.

11:50.343 --> 11:52.780
[ Earl Narrating ]
But Randy didn't wanna
go inside that night.

11:52.813 --> 11:54.915
He wanted to smoke.

11:57.885 --> 12:00.821
[ Clucking ]
Unfortunately,
he wasn't alone in the barn.

12:00.854 --> 12:02.489
[ Shouts ]

12:06.994 --> 12:09.429
There you go.
Now if you do it
to the other hand,

12:09.462 --> 12:13.433
I wanna take you
to my church so I can watch
all the old ladies cry.

12:13.466 --> 12:17.470
I'm sorry, Earl.
The good news is, you don't
have to put me on your list.

12:17.504 --> 12:21.308
It's not your fault
that this place didn't turn me
into a good person. It's mine.

12:21.341 --> 12:24.845
No, no. It's not my fault
you didn't turn out
like Bobby over there.

12:24.878 --> 12:29.516
It's your fault.
It's also your fault that
I didn't turn out like Bobby.

12:29.549 --> 12:34.121
- You want me to make a list
of my own and put you on it?
- No, I don't, Randy.

12:34.154 --> 12:37.791
You don't need to make a list.
Your list is right here.

12:37.825 --> 12:40.928
- This is your list.
- Not anymore it's not.
It's our list.

12:40.961 --> 12:43.230
Seeing how this place
coulda turned me around,

12:43.263 --> 12:47.234
I figure you're responsible
for everything bad I did
since the summer of 1982.

12:47.267 --> 12:49.136
And that's about 200 things.
Good luck.

12:53.106 --> 12:55.108
Stupid Carson Daly.

12:59.312 --> 13:01.548
[ Snores ]

13:01.581 --> 13:04.251
Wakey, wakey,
hands off snakey.

13:04.284 --> 13:08.055
- What are you doin'?
- Time to get up. Gotta get
started on your list.

13:08.088 --> 13:11.992
I chose the first one.
Took doughnuts from a bank
where I was not a customer.

13:12.025 --> 13:15.295
- Do I have to go now?
- Randy, people don't want their
doughnuts in the afternoon.

13:15.328 --> 13:18.098
Oh, sure they would.

13:18.131 --> 13:21.068
If you put gravy on 'em.
Or meat inside.

13:21.101 --> 13:24.137
With that smart frog
from Return of the Jedi
on my back.

13:24.171 --> 13:27.507
- [ Continues Snoring ]
- Randy, wake up.

13:27.540 --> 13:29.609
Poopie trim--
Huh?

13:29.642 --> 13:33.246
[ Chattering ]

13:35.415 --> 13:38.518
Can't I just leave 'em on
the table with the other stuff?
Nope.

13:38.551 --> 13:40.620
You gotta tell people
what you did
and why you're here.

13:40.653 --> 13:42.455
All of 'em?
All of 'em.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.593
- Everybody, listen up!
- [ Women Shrieking ]

13:48.295 --> 13:51.098
Drop the doughnuts!
Just drop the doughnuts.

13:51.131 --> 13:53.200
[ Woman Whimpers ]

13:58.305 --> 14:01.174
[ Earl Narrating ]
Randy spent the whole day
crossin' things off my list.

14:07.414 --> 14:10.884
My name in Earl,
and I stole this birdbath
out of a pickup truck...

14:10.918 --> 14:12.585
in the parking lot
of this building.

14:12.619 --> 14:14.554
Is it yours?

14:20.994 --> 14:23.563
[ Smacks Lips ]
Nope.

14:40.113 --> 14:42.983
This birdbath was stolen
out of the back
of a pickup truck--

14:43.016 --> 14:46.119
It is bad luck
to accept a birdbath
from a stranger.

14:48.488 --> 14:52.926
- [ Groaning ]
- My name is Earl.

14:52.960 --> 14:55.062
What up, Nescobar-A-Lop-Lop?

14:55.095 --> 14:57.164
[ Both Laugh ]

14:59.666 --> 15:02.469
[ Earl Narrating ]
It wasn't easy, but the hard
things in life never are.

15:02.502 --> 15:05.338
Randy was responsible
for who I became,

15:05.372 --> 15:07.975
and it was his job to make up
for everything bad I did.

15:09.276 --> 15:11.511
Sir, my name is Earl,

15:11.544 --> 15:14.381
and I slept with your wife.

15:14.414 --> 15:18.351
- [ Groans ]
- Was it in my own house?
In my own bed?

15:19.486 --> 15:22.122
Uh, I'll check.

15:31.698 --> 15:34.567
It was in your own house,
but it was on the couch,

15:34.601 --> 15:38.071
the counter,
the piano, the--
[ Groans ]

15:38.105 --> 15:40.740
Wait.
I've been married
a few times.

15:40.773 --> 15:43.410
Who are you
talking about?

15:43.443 --> 15:45.278
I'll find out.

15:57.090 --> 16:00.760
It was Sherry.
Sherry?
That's fine.

16:00.793 --> 16:03.396
If you had said Linda,
that'd be another story.

16:12.705 --> 16:16.109
Done.
He was okay with it
so long as it wasn't Linda.

16:16.143 --> 16:18.345
Check out number 188.

16:29.122 --> 16:31.591
[ Earl Narrating ]
It was relaxin' to have Randy
do my list for me.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.760
Kind of like a vacation.

16:33.793 --> 16:37.530
But then he came across
somethin' on the list
he couldn't do on his own.

16:37.564 --> 16:40.633
- I got one I can't do.
- Too bad.
Figure it out.

16:40.667 --> 16:43.103
I can't.
Number 98--

16:43.136 --> 16:45.672
told Dodge and Earl Jr.
we would have...

16:45.705 --> 16:48.275
a father-son day
at Mystery Fun Land
and didn't take them.

16:50.177 --> 16:52.112
[ Earl Narrating ]
I had promised the boys...

16:52.145 --> 16:54.214
I'd take them
to Mystery Fun Land.

16:54.247 --> 16:57.150
But I had also promised myself
I'd go to an AC/DC concert.

16:57.184 --> 17:01.388
- Hey, boys!
- You told us you would take us
to Mystery Fun Land.

17:01.421 --> 17:04.491
Front row.
They opened
with "Moneytalks."

17:09.096 --> 17:12.199
Well, I would have probably
taken 'em if I didn't get
kicked out of camp, Randy.

17:12.232 --> 17:14.701
I would have probably had
my own Mystery Fun Land.

17:14.734 --> 17:17.270
On my own private island.

17:17.304 --> 17:20.173
- The "Earlhamas."
- The "Earlhamas"?

17:20.207 --> 17:23.276
Yeah, maybe.
Maybe I'd be rich
and own a bunch of islands.

17:23.310 --> 17:25.312
Would there have been
an island for me?

17:25.345 --> 17:27.680
Yeah, probably.
Damn it.

17:27.714 --> 17:30.317
[ Woman Announcer On TV,
Indistinct ]

17:30.350 --> 17:35.188
Well, I can't fix this one.
They won't let me sign Dodge and
Earl Jr. out of bad kid camp.

17:35.222 --> 17:38.791
They say either you or Joy
or Darnell have to do it.

17:38.825 --> 17:40.660
[ Exhales ]

17:42.129 --> 17:44.397
Fine.
I'll do this one.

17:44.431 --> 17:47.367
But you gotta do another one
while I'm gone.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.469
Number 53--

17:49.502 --> 17:53.106
put used gum under almost
every table I've ever sat at.

17:53.140 --> 17:55.242
[ TV Continues,
Indistinct ]

17:59.379 --> 18:02.815
How am I supposed to know
which ones are "mines"
and which ones are yours?

18:04.551 --> 18:08.321
You kids ready
to have a good time?
[ Together ] Yeah!

18:08.355 --> 18:11.758
[ Earl Narrating ]
Me and the boys headed on down
to Mystery Fun Land.

18:11.791 --> 18:15.862
I figured after a couple hours
of Skee-Ball and a handful
of rides on the bumper cars,

18:15.895 --> 18:18.165
I'd be able
to cross 'em off my list...

18:18.198 --> 18:22.169
and get back to watchin'
buildings fall down on TV.

18:22.202 --> 18:25.838
However, there was
a small problem with that plan.

18:25.872 --> 18:27.907
Mystery Fun Land was gone.

18:27.940 --> 18:31.278
It's gone.
What?

18:31.311 --> 18:33.480
Mystery Fun Land.

18:33.513 --> 18:35.548
It's gone.
They tore it down.

18:37.517 --> 18:39.452
I can't cross you
off the list.

18:39.486 --> 18:41.688
You mean,
your idiot list?

18:41.721 --> 18:44.224
Is that what
your mom calls it?
Yeah.

18:44.257 --> 18:48.695
She puts another word
in front of idiot,
but I don't know what it means.

18:48.728 --> 18:50.897
The guy in Scarface
says it a lot.

18:50.930 --> 18:52.699
I know what it means.

18:52.732 --> 18:55.868
Yeah, my idiot list.

18:55.902 --> 18:59.739
You guys are on here
'cause I didn't take you
to Fun Land. You're number 98.

18:59.772 --> 19:03.576
But if there's no Fun Land,
there's no way
to cross you off.

19:03.610 --> 19:06.513
I don't know what
I'm supposed to do. This has
never happened before.

19:06.546 --> 19:08.915
What if we just forgive you?

19:08.948 --> 19:11.318
What?

19:11.351 --> 19:15.555
When someone tells the truth
and says they're sorry,
you forgive them.

19:15.588 --> 19:18.925
That's what we learned
at camp.

19:18.958 --> 19:21.428
[ Earl Narrating ]
That's when they made me
realize somethin'.

19:21.461 --> 19:24.364
It's never too late to make
the right choices in life.

19:24.397 --> 19:29.269
And forgivin' people you love--
Well, that's a right choice
I still hadn't made.

19:29.302 --> 19:33.373
If these little monsters
could forgive me, why couldn't
I forgive my own brother?

19:44.351 --> 19:49.422
- [ Sniffs ] Nicorette.
That's yours, Joy.
- Hey, doofus.

19:49.456 --> 19:51.958
If I wanted to see
that again, I wouldn't have
put it up under the table.

19:51.991 --> 19:54.361
Why don't you go
get started on the back
of my headboard?

19:54.394 --> 19:56.796
Anything that's grape
was put there by Earl.

19:59.999 --> 20:03.303
- Randy, you can stop now.
- I gotta go start
on the headboard.

20:03.336 --> 20:05.772
No, it's okay.
It's not your list anymore.

20:05.805 --> 20:08.007
I forgive you.
What?

20:08.040 --> 20:10.377
I know you're sorry
for what you did back then,

20:10.410 --> 20:12.645
and when somebody you love
is sorry, you forgive 'em.

20:12.679 --> 20:15.415
I am sorry I burned down
that barn, Earl.

20:15.448 --> 20:18.351
I know you are.
It's okay.

20:18.385 --> 20:21.754
Oh, my God.
You two are a couple
of fruits.

20:21.788 --> 20:24.357
I think it's sweet.

20:24.391 --> 20:26.793
Well, why don't y'all
go have a three-way?

20:26.826 --> 20:29.496
Pack of fruitcakes.

20:32.465 --> 20:35.402
I don't care
what she thinks.

20:35.435 --> 20:37.804
I don't either, Randy.

20:37.837 --> 20:39.939
My God,
I'm gonna vomit.

20:48.080 --> 20:50.049
Hey, Earl?

20:50.082 --> 20:52.485
Yeah, Randy?

20:52.519 --> 20:56.956
Do you think an ostrich
could get all the way here
from the Right Choice Ranch?

20:56.989 --> 21:00.860
Yeah. I mean, it could
probably walk that distance
if it really wanted to.

21:00.893 --> 21:04.431
But I think the chances of it
headin' in the right direction,
gettin' up the stairs...

21:04.464 --> 21:06.966
and findin' this particular room
are pretty slim.

21:19.111 --> 21:20.880
I'm gonna make sure
the door is locked.

21:24.417 --> 21:25.818
[ Door Lock Clicks ]
